{"url": "https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/ashley-judd-harvey-weinstein-interview_us_59f1cc1ee4b0438859158c49", "text": "Ashley Judd spoke out Thursday in her first TV appearance since publicly accusing film producer Harvey Weinstein of sexual harassment earlier this month.\n\nDuring an interview with ABC\u2019s Diane Sawyer, the \u201cDouble Jeopardy\u201d actress became emotional as she described Weinstein making unwanted sexual advances on her nearly two decades ago.\n\nAdvertisement\n\n\u201cI thought no meant no,\u201d Judd said during the interview, which aired on \u201cGood Morning America.\u201d \u201cI fought with this volley of no\u2019s, which he ignored.\u201d\n\n.@AshleyJudd on Harvey Weinstein encounter: \u201cIf I could go back retrospectively with a magic wand...I wish I could prevent it for anyone.\u201d pic.twitter.com/1NbOgJELeM \u2014 Good Morning America (@GMA) October 26, 2017\n\nJudd first described the encounter in a bombshell report published by The New York Times earlier this month. She told the Times that Weinstein sexually harassed her in his hotel room during what she believed would be a business meeting.\n\n\u201c[Weinstein] had her sent up to his room, where he appeared in a bathrobe and asked if he could give her a massage or she could watch him shower, she recalled in an interview,\u201d reported the Times.\n\n.@AshleyJudd on Harvey Weinstein: \u201cWhat I'd say to Harvey is I love you and I understand that you're sick...there's help for a guy like you\u201d pic.twitter.com/3mBkJQ8uMl \u2014 Good Morning America (@GMA) October 26, 2017\n\n\u201cI didn\u2019t expect that I would feel tearful,\u201d Judd told Sawyer, fighting back tears. \u201cBut it\u2019s been an absolutely, tremendously moving two and a half or three weeks.\u201d\n\nAdvertisement\n\nJudd said she could never forgive Weinstein for what he had done to women, and added that he \u201cabsolutely\u201d should go to jail if the sexual assault allegations against him are true.\n\nStill, Judd said she believes there is \u201chope and help\u201d for everyone, including sexual predators.\n\n\u201cThere has to be a real profound understanding on the part of the sexual predator that what he was doing was wrong and criminal,\u201d Judd said.\n\n\u201cWhat I would say to Harvey is, I love you and I understand you are sick and suffering,\u201d she added. \u201cAnd there is help for a guy like you, too. And it\u2019s entirely up to you to get that help.\u201d", "images": ["https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/62301f551e000050251b0362.jpg?cache=APRKCoD8Fe&ops=434_244%2Cquality_75", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/59ddd477140000a6234942ee.jpeg?ops=scalefit_960_noupscale", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/622d12b5230000d74f137446.jpeg?cache=Taj2XwFz53&ops=434_244%2Cquality_75", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/62307fce24000054bf96cb90.jpg?ops=240_240", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/623135492100009fca503cb0.jpeg?cache=bSYjRCerOc&ops=434_244%2Cquality_75", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/622f60fa1e0000ef251b02c3.jpeg?cache=eZvkzSTkoT&ops=240_240", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/62305bfc240000ff0f96cb6f.jpeg?cache=TE2kplL6Is&ops=434_244%2Cquality_75", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/6230c5142100000bc2503c63.jpeg?cache=dxDcy7OYeZ&ops=434_244%2Cquality_75", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/622b7f8924000052bf96c7fb.jpeg?cache=xfUoWi7fA5&ops=240_240", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/6230d32e240000ff0f96cc28.jpeg?ops=240_240", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/6230641a230000dc501376af.jpeg?ops=240_240", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/6230b4921e0000f2251b0445.jpeg?cache=FTmXN6f1Cu&ops=92_92", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/6230a8f11e0000f7251b042d.jpg?ops=434_244%2Cquality_75", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/622b62fb21000032a1503889.jpeg?cache=G3zBAEGGJF&ops=434_244%2Cquality_75", "https://img.huffingtonpost.com/asset/6230538f230000e050137695.png?cache=qXdTt0liih&ops=240_240